P[\text{k'th throw is first head}] = (1-p)^{k-1}p
P[\text{first head is on even throw}] = \sum_{k=1}^\infty (1-p)^{2k-1}p 
p(1-p)\sum_{k=0}^\infty (1-p)^{2k} = \frac{p(1-p)}{1-(1-p)^2} =\frac{1-p}{2-p} 
